                            <comment id="12696804" author="hossman" created="Tue, 7 Apr 2009 23:55:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;possible ways to resolve this...&lt;br/&gt;
1) add a comment clarifying that the current behavior is desired&lt;br/&gt;
2) make iteration start at &quot;1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
3) change getPowerOfTwoBucket so &quot;2&quot; is the lowest bucket value it ever returns.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12745131" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2009 18:09:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Should this be fixed for 1.4?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12745148" author="hossman" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2009 18:49:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;yeah ... fixing should be trivial, i just wasn&apos;t sure where the bug was (the iteration, or the bucket assignment)&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12747935" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 26 Aug 2009 14:19:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hoss, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you have a fix for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12748044" author="hossman" created="Wed, 26 Aug 2009 18:32:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;There were three possible fixes depending on what people thought the correct behavior should be. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i don&apos;t have the code in front of me, but as i recall they were all trivial...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) add a comment&lt;br/&gt;
2) change a for loop to start at 1 instead of 2&lt;br/&gt;
3) change getPowerOfTwoBucket to have something like...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; result &amp;lt; 2 ? 2 : result;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think Ryan wrote this code originally: Ryan, do you have any recollection as to what the orriginal intent was with the first bucket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12750212" author="hossman" created="Wed, 2 Sep 2009 01:57:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 810324.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i went ahead and fixed this using the &quot;display the &apos;1&apos; bucket&quot; approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775708" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:52:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
